HCC70 and Mesothelin (MSLN)

Introduction

Flow cytometry result link



Interestingly, these MSLN CAR-T escapers are TROP2 positive except #67 (Figure 1). Thus we can use TROP2 CAR-T cells to target these tumor cells.

For escapers #67, only about 56.5% are TROP2 positive and the remaining are TROP2 negative (Figure 1B). I sorted these two populations by flow cytometry and they showed quite different cell morphology (Figure 2) and STING expression (Figure 3). The TROP2 negative cells are almost STING negative (Figure 3).




The #67-1 and #67-2 display the different growth patterns on cultures.
Category TROP2 Positive TROP2 Negative
Cell Density Uniformly high; some cells are significantly larger. Extremely high; closely packed cells.
Cell Shape and Structure Large cells with clear boundaries and broad areas. Irregular shapes and sizes, some compressed.
Growth and Adaptation Strategies Vigorous growth and high adaptability. Adaptation to high density and irregular growth, maybe stressed?.

Email discussions

The ongoing experiments and plans includes: 1) As you suggested, I will confirm the MSLN level by qPCR assay. 2) I will validate that the TROP2 negative from escapers #67 are indeed tumor cells by STR genotyping. 3) As Thanh suggested, I labeled the TROP2 positive and TROP2 negative cells from escapers #67 with Luciferase and will compare their metastasis ability in vivo mice model.

Thanh said that there are breast cancer patients who are TROP2 negative. Thus, the question is how can we target and kill these TROP2-negative tumors? Unfortunately, we showed that these TROP2-negative tumor cells did not express other widely studied breast cancer-associated antigens, including MUC-1, ROR1, c-Met, and MICA/B (Figure 4). In addition, these TROP2-negative tumor cells are STING-negative(Figure 3).

Thus, can you please help dissect the differentially expressed genes (DEGs), upregulated and downregulated signaling between TROP2 high and TROP2 low tumor populations, as well as cell membrane proteins/receptor proteins that are highly expressed in the TROP2 low tumor populations?
